00:06:51.042 --> 00:06:53.065 align:middle line:84%
say sit back, relax,
go into a trance.

00:06:53.065 --> 00:06:53.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:06:53.940 --> 00:06:55.360 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Now
we've also got-- we

00:06:55.360 --> 00:06:57.080 align:middle line:84%
have different
styles of hypnosis.

00:06:57.080 --> 00:07:01.190 align:middle line:84%
Erickson was very
conversational and he

00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:03.820 align:middle line:84%
was very-- one of the things
that Erickson said was he said,

00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:05.380 align:middle line:84%
I think that a
client ought to be

00:07:05.380 --> 00:07:08.170 align:middle line:84%
able to go into a
trance in any way

00:07:08.170 --> 00:07:10.987 align:middle line:84%
that he or she chooses
to go into a trance,

00:07:10.987 --> 00:07:13.070 align:middle line:84%
and they ought to be able
to follow my suggestions

00:07:13.070 --> 00:07:14.940 align:middle line:84%
in any way that
he or she chooses

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:17.590 align:middle line:84%
to follow my suggestions,
which is a permissive--

00:07:17.590 --> 00:07:19.450 align:middle line:84%
and it's like, if you
think about what's

00:07:19.450 --> 00:07:22.064 align:middle line:84%
presupposed underneath that
is they're going in a trance

00:07:22.064 --> 00:07:23.480 align:middle line:84%
and they're following
suggestions.

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:23.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:24.506 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Right.

00:07:24.506 --> 00:07:26.920 align:middle line:84%
So it's a permissive
style of hypnosis.

00:07:26.920 --> 00:07:29.550 align:middle line:84%
But he was a kind man
with a-- you know,

00:07:29.550 --> 00:07:32.740 align:middle line:84%
he saw everybody as-- he thought
that everybody should have

00:07:32.740 --> 00:07:34.570 align:middle line:84%
a white house with
a white picket fence

00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:37.310 align:middle line:90%
and two kids and a dog.

00:07:37.310 --> 00:07:40.220 align:middle line:84%
And he helped people to
have that perfect life

00:07:40.220 --> 00:07:43.140 align:middle line:84%
as he envisioned it,
or as they obviously

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:45.280 align:middle line:84%
had to have their
own input, right.

00:07:45.280 --> 00:07:46.830 align:middle line:84%
And he would help
them to do that.

00:07:46.830 --> 00:07:49.460 align:middle line:84%
So he was coming from
a really good place,

00:07:49.460 --> 00:07:51.350 align:middle line:90%
but he was a magician of change.

00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:52.842 align:middle line:90%
And he'd do it linguistically.

00:07:52.842 --> 00:07:54.550 align:middle line:84%
Like you'd have a
conversation with him--

00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:54.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:07:54.960 --> 00:07:56.670 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -and you'd just
find yourself changing.

00:07:56.670 --> 00:07:57.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:58.868 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: That was
the magic of Erickson.

00:07:58.868 --> 00:08:01.550 align:middle line:84%
Like if you went to see
Erickson for smoking cessation,

00:08:01.550 --> 00:08:03.210 align:middle line:84%
to stop smoking,
he might not ever

00:08:03.210 --> 00:08:05.110 align:middle line:90%
talk about cigarettes directly.

00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:07.720 align:middle line:84%
He might tell you about a
story about a dog on a bluff

00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:09.940 align:middle line:84%
with a bone in its
mouth that wanted

00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:12.199 align:middle line:84%
to drink the cool
fresh water in a dish,

00:08:12.199 --> 00:08:13.990 align:middle line:84%
but it couldn't get to
the water because it

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:15.550 align:middle line:84%
didn't want to let
go of the bone.

00:08:15.550 --> 00:08:16.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:08:16.390 --> 00:08:18.556 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And then you find
yourself walking outside

00:08:18.556 --> 00:08:20.460 align:middle line:84%
and thinking about how
bad the therapy was

00:08:20.460 --> 00:08:21.720 align:middle line:84%
because the guy didn't
mention cigarettes,

00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:23.020 align:middle line:84%
and you'd forget to
do the old problem.

00:08:23.020 --> 00:08:24.020 align:middle line:90%
You'd forget to smoke.

00:08:24.020 --> 00:08:24.700 align:middle line:90%
It would be a trigger point.

00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:24.880 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:26.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ah,
brilliant, brilliant.

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:26.970 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Magician of change.

00:08:26.970 --> 00:08:28.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You studied
him for a long time.

00:08:28.510 --> 00:08:29.050 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Studied Erickson.

00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:31.840 align:middle line:84%
I study a lot of different types
of tools for transformation.

00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:36.309 align:middle line:84%
But ultimately, for me, it all
comes back to-- at some level,

00:08:36.309 --> 00:08:37.720 align:middle line:90%
it does come back to hypnosis.

00:08:37.720 --> 00:08:40.090 align:middle line:84%
And we're constantly using
hypnosis in our own life

00:08:40.090 --> 00:08:41.210 align:middle line:90%
anyway.

00:08:41.210 --> 00:08:43.985 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's like if somebody
doesn't stay on a diet,

00:08:43.985 --> 00:08:45.610 align:middle line:84%
it's because their
imagination kicks in

00:08:45.610 --> 00:08:47.800 align:middle line:84%
about how great the chocolate
cake's going to taste.

00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:48.383 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:08:48.383 --> 00:08:50.490 align:middle line:84%
So that's a self-hypnosis
in the wrong direction.

00:08:50.490 --> 00:08:51.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Exactly.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:51.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:08:51.370 --> 00:08:52.120 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Exactly.

00:08:52.120 --> 00:08:54.894 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But can we take our--
say we want to stay on a diet

00:08:54.894 --> 00:08:57.060 align:middle line:84%
and we would look at that
picture of the bikini body

00:08:57.060 --> 00:08:58.070 align:middle line:84%
that we put up on
our refrigerator.

00:08:58.070 --> 00:08:59.194 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: That's what I do.

00:08:59.194 --> 00:09:01.270 align:middle line:84%
I look at the bikini body
and I say, I want it.

00:09:01.270 --> 00:09:02.353 align:middle line:90%
That's how I want to look.

00:09:02.353 --> 00:09:03.750 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:05.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you put
in the refrigerator,

00:09:05.800 --> 00:09:08.366 align:middle line:84%
but I open it and still
reach for whatever

00:09:08.366 --> 00:09:10.740 align:middle line:84%
is in there that isn't going
to give you the bikini body.

00:09:10.740 --> 00:09:12.010 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: You reached
right past the bikini body?

00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:12.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I did.

00:09:12.310 --> 00:09:13.184 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Oh, my God.

00:09:13.184 --> 00:09:14.020 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

00:09:14.020 --> 00:09:14.540 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:09:14.540 --> 00:09:16.474 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But that obviously
didn't work for me.

00:09:16.474 --> 00:09:17.140 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Right.

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:17.764 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So--

00:09:17.764 --> 00:09:19.930 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: I mean, it's like,
did it not work for you

00:09:19.930 --> 00:09:21.170 align:middle line:90%
or did you not work it?

00:09:21.170 --> 00:09:23.979 align:middle line:84%
Because there's always--
whenever-- whenever change--

00:09:23.979 --> 00:09:26.270 align:middle line:84%
whenever we're talking about
change and transformation,

00:09:26.270 --> 00:09:30.890 align:middle line:84%
there's two things that
play-- interweave together.

00:09:30.890 --> 00:09:33.390 align:middle line:84%
We've got willpower and
we've got imagination.

00:09:33.390 --> 00:09:34.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:34.530 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:34.530 --> 00:09:35.030 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:09:35.030 --> 00:09:35.550 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:09:35.550 --> 00:09:37.547 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So like I tell
people with smoking,

00:09:37.547 --> 00:09:39.880 align:middle line:84%
because I just finished a
class out here in Los Angeles.

00:09:39.880 --> 00:09:42.117 align:middle line:84%
We had 600 people in
the class, big class,

00:09:42.117 --> 00:09:44.700 align:middle line:84%
they were all becoming certified
in transformational hypnosis.

00:09:44.700 --> 00:09:45.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nice.

00:09:45.220 --> 00:09:46.595 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Yeah,
it was very cool.

00:09:46.595 --> 00:09:47.890 align:middle line:90%
It was good fun.

00:09:47.890 --> 00:09:50.400 align:middle line:84%
And when we did the class,
one of the things I say

00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:53.230 align:middle line:84%
is that whenever willpower and
imagination are in conflict,

00:09:53.230 --> 00:09:55.440 align:middle line:90%
imagination will always win.

00:09:55.440 --> 00:09:55.940 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:09:55.940 --> 00:09:57.670 align:middle line:90%
Because-- and that's how it is.

00:09:57.670 --> 00:09:59.492 align:middle line:84%
If you don't stay
in the relationship

00:09:59.492 --> 00:10:01.450 align:middle line:84%
it's because you're
imagining that the grass is

00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:03.350 align:middle line:90%
greener on the other side.

00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:03.930 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:10:03.930 --> 00:10:03.970 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps.

00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:06.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or if you don't have
a big enough imagination

00:10:06.370 --> 00:10:09.070 align:middle line:84%
around what the body could look
like, the imagination of how

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:11.015 align:middle line:84%
the cake will make
you feel is bigger.

00:10:11.015 --> 00:10:11.700 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're saying?

00:10:11.700 --> 00:10:14.075 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Well, that's what
happened in your case, right?

00:10:14.075 --> 00:10:15.980 align:middle line:84%
Because either your
willpower wasn't in check

00:10:15.980 --> 00:10:17.563 align:middle line:84%
where you weren't
being an participate

00:10:17.563 --> 00:10:21.360 align:middle line:84%
in the-- active
participant in the change.

00:10:21.360 --> 00:10:22.902 align:middle line:84%
You were just looking
at the-- you're

00:10:22.902 --> 00:10:24.818 align:middle line:84%
looking at the body
going, yeah, I'd like that

00:10:24.818 --> 00:10:26.580 align:middle line:84%
but I want that
chocolate cake more.

00:10:26.580 --> 00:10:28.770 align:middle line:84%
Or-- so the willpower's
is not in check there.

00:10:28.770 --> 00:10:32.296 align:middle line:84%
Or your imagination is
bigger-- you perceive

00:10:32.296 --> 00:10:34.670 align:middle line:84%
there to be a bigger benefit
from the cake in the moment.

00:10:34.670 --> 00:10:36.540 align:middle line:84%
And there's ways that
you can change that.

00:10:36.540 --> 00:10:38.206 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The secondary
gain was comfort.

00:10:38.206 --> 00:10:39.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: The emotional
benefit, right.

00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:41.955 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then I could go
after, what, the comfort

00:10:41.955 --> 00:10:44.120 align:middle line:84%
and how that would
feel when I really

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:46.594 align:middle line:90%
have the diet that I want.

00:10:46.594 --> 00:10:47.260 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Right.

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:50.344 align:middle line:84%
Or how great will you feel
that emotional benefit when you

00:10:50.344 --> 00:10:52.010 align:middle line:84%
really-- when you're
lean and trim and--

00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:52.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:10:52.460 --> 00:10:54.126 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -and you
get that bikini body.

00:10:54.126 --> 00:10:57.470 align:middle line:84%
And it sounds-- it's simpler--
you know, people go easier

00:10:57.470 --> 00:10:58.617 align:middle line:90%
said than done, right?

00:10:58.617 --> 00:10:59.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:01.960 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Because in the moment
we have emotional triggers that

00:11:01.960 --> 00:11:04.550 align:middle line:90%
trigger responses--

00:11:04.550 --> 00:11:06.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's all that.

00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:08.730 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -whether it be eating
to anesthetize our emotions

00:11:08.730 --> 00:11:10.780 align:middle line:84%
or it be spending too
much or watching too much

00:11:10.780 --> 00:11:13.910 align:middle line:84%
TV or drinking or drugs
or whatever people

00:11:13.910 --> 00:11:16.320 align:middle line:84%
do to anesthetize
their emotions and not

00:11:16.320 --> 00:11:17.942 align:middle line:90%
deal with the things at hand.

00:11:17.942 --> 00:11:20.150 align:middle line:84%
But that's their imagination
getting the best of them

00:11:20.150 --> 00:11:20.650 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:11:20.650 --> 00:11:23.585 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not preaching
at anybody because I've

00:11:23.585 --> 00:11:24.960 align:middle line:84%
been in all those
same positions.

00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:25.350 align:middle line:90%
We all are.

00:11:25.350 --> 00:11:25.940 align:middle line:90%
This is life.

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:26.640 align:middle line:90%
We're human beings.

00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:27.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:11:27.200 --> 00:11:27.700 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:11:27.700 --> 00:11:30.690 align:middle line:84%
But you happen to have some-- a
tool or skill set here that can

00:11:30.690 --> 00:11:32.725 align:middle line:84%
really help guide people
out of those triggers--

00:11:32.725 --> 00:11:33.850 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah, absolutely.

00:11:33.850 --> 00:11:35.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: -which is great.

00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:37.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And once again,
I've had to guide myself out

00:11:37.940 --> 00:11:40.810 align:middle line:84%
of my own triggers and I've
had to continually do that

00:11:40.810 --> 00:11:44.290 align:middle line:84%
throughout life, because life is
a process of having challenges.

00:11:44.290 --> 00:11:47.880 align:middle line:84%
But when we got great tools,
we are more well-equipped

00:11:47.880 --> 00:11:49.860 align:middle line:84%
and more ready to deal
with those things.

00:11:49.860 --> 00:11:52.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So can you give
us an example of what--

00:11:52.640 --> 00:11:57.240 align:middle line:84%
some simple examples of how we
could use hypnosis in our life?

00:11:57.240 --> 00:12:00.120 align:middle line:84%
Like, something that shows
us that we're good at it?

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:01.870 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: I mean,
it's across the board,

00:12:01.870 --> 00:12:04.250 align:middle line:84%
because-- and by the
way, the question really

00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:06.980 align:middle line:84%
becomes when do we not
use hypnosis in our life?

00:12:06.980 --> 00:12:10.300 align:middle line:84%
We are constantly
using-- and this

00:12:10.300 --> 00:12:12.690 align:middle line:84%
is what I look to drill
into people's heads

00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:15.920 align:middle line:84%
is that there's never a moment
that you're not hypnotized.

00:12:15.920 --> 00:12:16.460 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:12:16.460 --> 00:12:19.090 align:middle line:84%
Because you're mistaking
the map for the territory.

00:12:19.090 --> 00:12:21.750 align:middle line:84%
You're mistaking your model
of the world, your beliefs,

00:12:21.750 --> 00:12:23.857 align:middle line:90%
your values as being real.

00:12:23.857 --> 00:12:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:25.065 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:12:25.065 --> 00:12:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a
unique individual way

00:12:27.260 --> 00:12:29.540 align:middle line:84%
of looking at the world,
but it's not real.

00:12:29.540 --> 00:12:30.660 align:middle line:90%
Reality is subjective.

00:12:30.660 --> 00:12:31.984 align:middle line:90%
We each have our own reality.

00:12:31.984 --> 00:12:34.150 align:middle line:84%
All right, so we're mistaking
our model of the world

00:12:34.150 --> 00:12:37.720 align:middle line:84%
for being real, so we're
constantly hypnotized anyway.

00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:39.990 align:middle line:84%
And then the thoughts
that we have either

00:12:39.990 --> 00:12:42.030 align:middle line:84%
hypnotize us to produce
extraordinary results

00:12:42.030 --> 00:12:45.520 align:middle line:84%
or to produce ordinary results
or below average results.

00:12:45.520 --> 00:12:48.500 align:middle line:84%
So I kind of joke
with people sometimes,

00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:51.000 align:middle line:84%
I say when you think about going
to the gym and working out,

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:54.440 align:middle line:84%
you know, are you your
own best coach mentally?

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:55.870 align:middle line:90%
Are you going, I'm going to gym.

00:12:55.870 --> 00:12:56.620 align:middle line:90%
You're an athlete.

00:12:56.620 --> 00:12:57.328 align:middle line:90%
You're a warrior.

00:12:57.328 --> 00:12:58.050 align:middle line:90%
You enjoy this.

00:12:58.050 --> 00:12:59.250 align:middle line:90%
You love working out.

00:12:59.250 --> 00:12:59.950 align:middle line:90%
You enjoy it.

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:01.810 align:middle line:90%
You love eating right.

00:13:01.810 --> 00:13:03.350 align:middle line:90%
You eat healthy.

00:13:03.350 --> 00:13:06.140 align:middle line:84%
Imagine yourself right
now lean and trim.

00:13:06.140 --> 00:13:07.340 align:middle line:90%
You are an athlete.

00:13:07.340 --> 00:13:09.770 align:middle line:84%
You're a warrior and
you love to workout.

00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:11.800 align:middle line:84%
You wake up early
and it feels good.

00:13:11.800 --> 00:13:15.141 align:middle line:84%
And you hear the voice-- is that
the dialogue that's going on

00:13:15.141 --> 00:13:15.640 align:middle line:90%
inside?

00:13:15.640 --> 00:13:17.930 align:middle line:84%
Are those the pictures
that are going on inside?

00:13:17.930 --> 00:13:20.180 align:middle line:84%
Or is it like, well, you
wake up in the morning

00:13:20.180 --> 00:13:21.430 align:middle line:90%
and your alarm clock goes off.

00:13:21.430 --> 00:13:24.774 align:middle line:84%
Well, sleep's an important
part of health, too.

00:13:24.774 --> 00:13:25.274 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:13:25.274 --> 00:13:26.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:13:26.060 --> 00:13:26.560 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:26.560 --> 00:13:27.552 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:13:27.552 --> 00:13:28.760 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: It's your thoughts.

00:13:28.760 --> 00:13:29.551 align:middle line:90%
It's your thoughts.

00:13:29.551 --> 00:13:32.870 align:middle line:84%
So it comes down to our
thoughts govern our reality.

00:13:32.870 --> 00:13:35.160 align:middle line:84%
It's the same thing that
Napoleon Hill was saying back

00:13:35.160 --> 00:13:36.201 align:middle line:90%
in "Think and Grow Rich."

00:13:36.201 --> 00:13:37.770 align:middle line:84%
It's the same thing
then Rhonda Byrne

00:13:37.770 --> 00:13:39.090 align:middle line:90%
was saying in "The Secret."

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:41.890 align:middle line:84%
It's the same thing, but
very few people really

00:13:41.890 --> 00:13:44.370 align:middle line:84%
understand how do you
take charge of that?

00:13:44.370 --> 00:13:46.390 align:middle line:84%
And here's where hypnosis
comes into the picture

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:49.000 align:middle line:84%
because we've all
heard that we only

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:52.454 align:middle line:84%
use 10% percent of our mind,
but neurobiologists these days

00:13:52.454 --> 00:13:53.870 align:middle line:84%
are saying that
it's only about 5%

00:13:53.870 --> 00:13:56.780 align:middle line:84%
of who we are that one would
consider to be conscious.

00:13:56.780 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:84%
So 95% of who we are
would be unconscious.

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:01.600 align:middle line:90%
That's the body mind.

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:03.355 align:middle line:84%
The part of you that beats
your heart, that blinks you,

00:14:03.355 --> 00:14:05.360 align:middle line:84%
that circulate your
lymph, that breathes you.

00:14:05.360 --> 00:14:06.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 95%?

00:14:06.290 --> 00:14:07.250 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: 95%.

00:14:07.250 --> 00:14:09.590 align:middle line:84%
So people go out and they
say, yeah, I read the book

00:14:09.590 --> 00:14:12.860 align:middle line:84%
or I saw the DVD and I'm
using the Law of Attraction,

00:14:12.860 --> 00:14:13.910 align:middle line:90%
for example, which is--

00:14:13.910 --> 00:14:14.451 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:14:14.451 --> 00:14:16.290 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -it's
absolutely- it's gospel;

00:14:16.290 --> 00:14:19.250 align:middle line:84%
however, they're doing it
with 5% of who they are.

00:14:19.250 --> 00:14:20.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 5% isn't enough.

00:14:20.730 --> 00:14:22.380 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: 5% is
not enough, right?

00:14:22.380 --> 00:14:22.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:24.665 align:middle line:84%
That's not enough
inertia there at all.

00:14:24.665 --> 00:14:25.290 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:14:25.290 --> 00:14:28.420 align:middle line:84%
So it's like where's
the other 95% going?

00:14:28.420 --> 00:14:31.015 align:middle line:84%
And if you have a goal
and you set a goal

00:14:31.015 --> 00:14:32.390 align:middle line:84%
that you want to
make more money,

00:14:32.390 --> 00:14:33.973 align:middle line:84%
but if at the
unconscious level you've

00:14:33.973 --> 00:14:35.826 align:middle line:84%
got anger toward
people who make money

00:14:35.826 --> 00:14:37.450 align:middle line:84%
or you've got guilt
about making money,

00:14:37.450 --> 00:14:39.780 align:middle line:84%
like you feel at some level it's
not spiritual to make money.

00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:40.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:43.091 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Or you have fear about
what making money would mean

00:14:43.091 --> 00:14:47.092 align:middle line:84%
or false associations like money
is evil or money and happiness

00:14:47.092 --> 00:14:48.050 align:middle line:90%
don't go hand in hand--

00:14:48.050 --> 00:14:48.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:14:48.700 --> 00:14:50.949 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -then that past
programming and conditioning

00:14:50.949 --> 00:14:53.810 align:middle line:84%
is going to override any
conscious goal that you

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:54.620 align:middle line:90%
might have.

00:14:54.620 --> 00:14:57.531 align:middle line:84%
And if you go-- it's the
same with relationships.

00:14:57.531 --> 00:14:59.655 align:middle line:84%
You know, if you have a
goal to have a relationship

00:14:59.655 --> 00:15:01.550 align:middle line:84%
and you say, boy, I want to
have that great relationship.

00:15:01.550 --> 00:15:03.025 align:middle line:84%
But if at the
unconscious level you

00:15:03.025 --> 00:15:04.483 align:middle line:84%
have anger toward
the opposite sex,

00:15:04.483 --> 00:15:07.370 align:middle line:84%
you've got guilt from
past relationships, fear

00:15:07.370 --> 00:15:09.910 align:middle line:84%
of abandonment,
fear of intimacy,

00:15:09.910 --> 00:15:12.300 align:middle line:84%
or even both where it's
like don't come too close

00:15:12.300 --> 00:15:13.130 align:middle line:90%
but don't go away.

00:15:13.130 --> 00:15:13.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:15:13.730 --> 00:15:14.060 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:15.030 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Those
push-pull conflicts

00:15:15.030 --> 00:15:16.780 align:middle line:84%
stop people dead
in their tracks.

00:15:16.780 --> 00:15:19.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So can we
find a way to know

00:15:19.120 --> 00:15:22.310 align:middle line:84%
if we are suggestible
enough for hypnosis?

00:15:22.310 --> 00:15:26.780 align:middle line:84%
Does everybody get-- is able--
they're able to get hypnotized

00:15:26.780 --> 00:15:28.780 align:middle line:84%
or is there a way that
we could figure that out?

00:15:28.780 --> 00:15:30.404 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: It's an
interesting question,

00:15:30.404 --> 00:15:32.545 align:middle line:84%
if we're suggestible
enough for hypnosis.

00:15:32.545 --> 00:15:34.510 align:middle line:84%
There was a couple
called the Hilgards that

00:15:34.510 --> 00:15:37.335 align:middle line:84%
did some research
way back in the day.

00:15:37.335 --> 00:15:38.990 align:middle line:90%
That means a long time ago.

00:15:38.990 --> 00:15:41.280 align:middle line:84%
And what they did was they
took people off the street

00:15:41.280 --> 00:15:42.910 align:middle line:84%
and they played a
phonograph record,

00:15:42.910 --> 00:15:44.743 align:middle line:84%
and they wanted to see
how many people would

00:15:44.743 --> 00:15:46.210 align:middle line:84%
go into trance by
simply listening

00:15:46.210 --> 00:15:47.437 align:middle line:90%
to the photographic record.

00:15:47.437 --> 00:15:49.770 align:middle line:84%
And they found that a certain
percent of people would go

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:52.510 align:middle line:84%
into a light hypnotic
trance, a certain percent--

00:15:52.510 --> 00:15:54.780 align:middle line:84%
I think it was 20%
into a light trance,

00:15:54.780 --> 00:15:59.440 align:middle line:84%
60% into a medium trance,
another 20% into a heavier--

00:15:59.440 --> 00:16:00.560 align:middle line:90%
a deep state of trance--

00:16:00.560 --> 00:16:01.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:02.290 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -by simply
listening to the record.

00:16:02.290 --> 00:16:04.081 align:middle line:84%
But the problem with
the Hilgard's research

00:16:04.081 --> 00:16:07.370 align:middle line:84%
was that they took one important
part out of the equation, which

00:16:07.370 --> 00:16:10.190 align:middle line:90%
was the teacher of the hypnosis.

00:16:10.190 --> 00:16:12.930 align:middle line:84%
And we say that all
hypnosis is about learning

00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:15.140 align:middle line:90%
how to go into hypnosis.

00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:17.760 align:middle line:90%
So anybody can be taught trance.

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:21.090 align:middle line:84%
Anybody can be taught
to utilize the power

00:16:21.090 --> 00:16:23.917 align:middle line:90%
of their unconscious mind.

00:16:23.917 --> 00:16:26.000 align:middle line:84%
Because when you align
your conscious intentions--

00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:27.710 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -with your
unconscious resources,

00:16:27.710 --> 00:16:29.251 align:middle line:84%
that's where you
get 100% of yourself

00:16:29.251 --> 00:16:30.360 align:middle line:90%
moving toward your goals.

00:16:30.360 --> 00:16:30.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nice.

00:16:30.820 --> 00:16:32.040 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Physically,
emotionally,

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:32.850 align:middle line:90%
spiritually, financially.

00:16:32.850 --> 00:16:34.040 align:middle line:84%
If you want to make
more money, if you

00:16:34.040 --> 00:16:34.760 align:middle line:84%
want to have better
relationships.

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:36.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have
to know your goals.

00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:37.306 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Well, you
have to know your goals,

00:16:37.306 --> 00:16:40.240 align:middle line:84%
you have to get clear, so that's
why we say that intention--

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:40.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:16:40.740 --> 00:16:42.550 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -is the most
important aspect of hypnosis.

00:16:42.550 --> 00:16:44.008 align:middle line:84%
And back to your
original question,

00:16:44.008 --> 00:16:46.530 align:middle line:84%
what's the difference between
stage and therapeutic hypnosis

00:16:46.530 --> 00:16:47.670 align:middle line:90%
would be the intention.

00:16:47.670 --> 00:16:48.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:16:48.210 --> 00:16:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Stage hypnosis, the
intention is to entertain.

00:16:50.240 --> 00:16:50.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:16:50.550 --> 00:16:50.880 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:16:50.880 --> 00:16:51.210 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:16:51.210 --> 00:16:52.790 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: People follow
suggestions for that.

00:16:52.790 --> 00:16:55.100 align:middle line:84%
Therapeutic hypnosis, it
could be to make more money,

00:16:55.100 --> 00:16:56.570 align:middle line:84%
could be to improve
your relationships--

00:16:56.570 --> 00:16:56.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Transform.

00:16:56.950 --> 00:16:58.060 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -transform
in some way.

00:16:58.060 --> 00:16:59.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In any way.

00:16:59.050 --> 00:17:00.690 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And so
when you-- the person

00:17:00.690 --> 00:17:03.330 align:middle line:84%
who's the teacher-- so as a
teacher of hypnosis, what you

00:17:03.330 --> 00:17:06.980 align:middle line:84%
do is you teach people
how to access the deepest

00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:08.869 align:middle line:84%
resources of their
unconscious mind

00:17:08.869 --> 00:17:12.151 align:middle line:84%
so that they have 100%
control over their own life.

00:17:12.151 --> 00:17:14.609 align:middle line:84%
Because when you can give your
body, your unconscious mind,

00:17:14.609 --> 00:17:17.281 align:middle line:84%
the suggestion to shut
off pain and it does--

00:17:17.281 --> 00:17:17.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:17:17.780 --> 00:17:18.359 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: -that's power.

00:17:18.359 --> 00:17:18.859 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:18.859 --> 00:17:20.859 align:middle line:84%
Or to stop smoking,
which could kill you.

00:17:20.859 --> 00:17:21.810 align:middle line:90%
And there's so much.

00:17:21.810 --> 00:17:23.579 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Or to fall in
love with making cold calls,

00:17:23.579 --> 00:17:24.099 align:middle line:90%
and it does.

00:17:24.099 --> 00:17:25.970 align:middle line:84%
I always-- I tell
people, I say, if you

00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:27.990 align:middle line:84%
fell in love with working
out and eating right,

00:17:27.990 --> 00:17:30.630 align:middle line:84%
do you think you'd be
10 times healthier?

00:17:30.630 --> 00:17:31.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, of course.

00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Because-- yes, love is
a very powerful feeling.

00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:35.306 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: It's a
powerful emotion.

00:17:35.306 --> 00:17:37.564 align:middle line:84%
If you fell in love with
marketing and advertising

00:17:37.564 --> 00:17:39.230 align:middle line:84%
your business and
doing sales, would you

00:17:39.230 --> 00:17:40.740 align:middle line:84%
be 10 times more
successful financially--

00:17:40.740 --> 00:17:41.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:41.090 --> 00:17:41.881 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: -or more?

00:17:41.881 --> 00:17:42.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:44.160 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: If you fell in love
with fulfilling your partner,

00:17:44.160 --> 00:17:45.880 align:middle line:84%
would have a better
relationship, right?

00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:46.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:48.020 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So-- and
all of these things

00:17:48.020 --> 00:17:49.394 align:middle line:84%
are a function of
the imagination

00:17:49.394 --> 00:17:52.000 align:middle line:84%
and all of these things
can be done with hypnosis.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:54.450 align:middle line:84%
And, as a matter of
fact, I'd go so far

00:17:54.450 --> 00:17:57.480 align:middle line:84%
as to say they are already
being done with hypnosis,

00:17:57.480 --> 00:17:58.970 align:middle line:90%
just probably not so well.

00:17:58.970 --> 00:18:00.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In-- or in the
opposite direction.

00:18:00.720 --> 00:18:00.890 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: In the
opposite direction.

00:18:00.890 --> 00:18:02.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A lot of
marketing and sales

00:18:02.580 --> 00:18:04.550 align:middle line:90%
are all hypnosis, basically.

00:18:04.550 --> 00:18:07.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's the way
that you're shown

00:18:07.730 --> 00:18:09.787 align:middle line:84%
that you'll have this
body if you buy this.

00:18:09.787 --> 00:18:11.370 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Imagine
this body, buy this.

00:18:11.370 --> 00:18:13.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Martin
Luther King, Jr, one

00:18:13.180 --> 00:18:15.875 align:middle line:84%
of the best hypnotists of
all time one could say.

00:18:15.875 --> 00:18:16.375 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:18:16.375 --> 00:18:17.416 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: I have a dream.

00:18:17.416 --> 00:18:20.990 align:middle line:84%
He took people from a state, an
emotional state of resignation

00:18:20.990 --> 00:18:23.500 align:middle line:84%
to a state of inspiration, and
they changed their behaviors

00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:25.620 align:middle line:84%
and went out and changed
the face of a nation.

00:18:25.620 --> 00:18:27.240 align:middle line:84%
Through the dream,
through the imagery

00:18:27.240 --> 00:18:29.640 align:middle line:84%
that he was able to
paint for people,

00:18:29.640 --> 00:18:31.680 align:middle line:84%
he was able to spark
that and that's really

00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:32.786 align:middle line:90%
how hypnosis works.

00:18:32.786 --> 00:18:34.660 align:middle line:84%
It's about creating
thoughts in the mind that

00:18:34.660 --> 00:18:38.500 align:middle line:84%
are so real that we generate
emotions in our body.

00:18:38.500 --> 00:18:42.910 align:middle line:84%
And an emotion-- emotion is
like, it's behind all motion.

00:18:42.910 --> 00:18:43.469 align:middle line:90%
It's the--

00:18:43.469 --> 00:18:44.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Energy in motion.

00:18:44.510 --> 00:18:45.634 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Energy in motion.

00:18:45.634 --> 00:18:49.280 align:middle line:84%
It's what creates our behavioral
states or our behaviors.

00:18:49.280 --> 00:18:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And our behaviors ultimately
determine our outcomes.

00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:53.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So there's something
fun that you do and we're going

00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:55.740 align:middle line:84%
to have someone on that's
going to come on later

00:18:55.740 --> 00:18:57.440 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to actually
work with this person--

00:18:57.440 --> 00:18:57.700 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:18:57.700 --> 00:19:00.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: -to show what it means
to go into a hypnotic state.

00:19:00.270 --> 00:19:00.890 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: We can do that, yes.

00:19:00.890 --> 00:19:03.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And we're going to show
a few videos around that, too.

00:19:03.270 --> 00:19:05.340 align:middle line:84%
But let's-- you have a
little technique that--

00:19:05.340 --> 00:19:07.465 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Oh, you want to
do a suggestibility test.

00:19:07.465 --> 00:19:09.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, I do,
so play along here.

00:19:09.150 --> 00:19:10.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Oh, if you want
