>>HOWARD: When you do-- and you
can do this at home, too-- when

00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:12.960 align:middle line:84%
you do, I want you to watch
the space between your fingers

00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:15.090 align:middle line:84%
and imagine and pretend--
and you have to do this.

00:20:15.090 --> 00:20:15.740 align:middle line:90%
I can't do it for you.

00:20:15.740 --> 00:20:16.780 align:middle line:84%
You have to fully
imagine and pretend

00:20:16.780 --> 00:20:18.790 align:middle line:84%
that I put a vise
clamp on your fingers

00:20:18.790 --> 00:20:20.900 align:middle line:84%
and I want you to watch
them draw together.

00:20:20.900 --> 00:20:23.051 align:middle line:84%
So go ahead right now
and open your fingers

00:20:23.051 --> 00:20:24.800 align:middle line:84%
and watch the space
between them and watch

00:20:24.800 --> 00:20:27.980 align:middle line:84%
them coming closer and closer,
tighter and tighter, closer

00:20:27.980 --> 00:20:28.480 align:middle line:90%
and closer.

00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:29.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm coming closer to you.

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:31.420 align:middle line:84%
Tighter and tighter,
closer and closer.

00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:32.620 align:middle line:90%
Allow it to happen.

00:20:32.620 --> 00:20:33.610 align:middle line:90%
Want it to happen.

00:20:33.610 --> 00:20:35.020 align:middle line:90%
Will it to happen.

00:20:35.020 --> 00:20:38.120 align:middle line:84%
Remember, you have to do
this, I can't do it for you.

00:20:38.120 --> 00:20:39.990 align:middle line:84%
So bringing all the
way together now,

00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:42.350 align:middle line:84%
coming all the way together,
closer and closer, tighter

00:20:42.350 --> 00:20:43.250 align:middle line:90%
and tighter.

00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:44.940 align:middle line:84%
Tighter and tighter,
closer and closer.

00:20:44.940 --> 00:20:47.630 align:middle line:84%
Keep them going now, tighter
and tighter, closer and closer.

00:20:47.630 --> 00:20:48.400 align:middle line:90%
[LISA LAUGHS]

00:20:48.400 --> 00:20:50.730 align:middle line:84%
OK, the audience--
anybody watching at home,

00:20:50.730 --> 00:20:52.210 align:middle line:90%
you can stop, but not Lisa.

00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:53.836 align:middle line:84%
Tighter and tighter,
closer and closer.

00:20:53.836 --> 00:20:54.335 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:20:54.335 --> 00:20:56.450 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Tighter and
tighter, closer and closer.

00:20:56.450 --> 00:20:57.590 align:middle line:90%
Tighter and tighter.

00:20:57.590 --> 00:21:01.361 align:middle line:84%
Now I want you to try to open
them and find that you can't.

00:21:01.361 --> 00:21:02.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so weird!

00:21:02.440 --> 00:21:03.730 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Free movement
returns to your hands.

00:21:03.730 --> 00:21:04.090 align:middle line:90%
Yes, right.

00:21:04.090 --> 00:21:05.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so weird, yes.

00:21:05.340 --> 00:21:07.550 align:middle line:84%
I was looking at you and
a part of me was like, OK,

00:21:07.550 --> 00:21:09.630 align:middle line:90%
this is not-- yeah.

00:21:09.630 --> 00:21:10.590 align:middle line:90%
There's really the--

00:21:10.590 --> 00:21:11.800 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: It's a
teaching tool, yeah.

00:21:11.800 --> 00:21:12.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:21:12.130 --> 00:21:14.840 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: It's not that somebody
couldn't force it open and go,

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:16.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
move my fingers.

00:21:16.040 --> 00:21:17.000 align:middle line:90%
Of course they could.

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:19.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you said I have
to be willing to do this.

00:21:19.450 --> 00:21:20.630 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And that's
the thing with hypnosis

00:21:20.630 --> 00:21:22.930 align:middle line:84%
is that people-- we've got
to change the way that people

00:21:22.930 --> 00:21:23.554 align:middle line:90%
think about it.

00:21:23.554 --> 00:21:27.670 align:middle line:84%
They think that it's subjugating
your control to somebody else

00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:29.310 align:middle line:90%
and that's not the case.

00:21:29.310 --> 00:21:32.450 align:middle line:84%
What it is, is it's allowing
you-- it's allowing you--

00:21:32.450 --> 00:21:34.190 align:middle line:84%
or you're allowing
yourself to get

00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:36.806 align:middle line:84%
rid of what we call
the critical faculty.

00:21:36.806 --> 00:21:38.430 align:middle line:84%
The critical faculty
is the part of you

00:21:38.430 --> 00:21:40.600 align:middle line:84%
that distinguishes
fantasy from reality.

00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:43.290 align:middle line:84%
It's the-- we develop it
right around the age of seven

00:21:43.290 --> 00:21:43.850 align:middle line:90%
to nine.

00:21:43.850 --> 00:21:45.525 align:middle line:84%
And it's the part of
you that says yeah,

00:21:45.525 --> 00:21:47.390 align:middle line:84%
I buy that, yeah,
I believe that,

00:21:47.390 --> 00:21:49.700 align:middle line:84%
or no, I don't
believe that, right?

00:21:49.700 --> 00:21:54.024 align:middle line:84%
So it's-- if you could imagine
a circle and you've got

00:21:54.024 --> 00:21:55.940 align:middle line:84%
your conscious mind and
your unconscious mind,

00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:58.660 align:middle line:84%
and it's split in half
with the critical faculty.

00:21:58.660 --> 00:22:01.130 align:middle line:84%
Well-- or it would be
split at 5%, right?

00:22:01.130 --> 00:22:03.260 align:middle line:90%
Because 95% is unconscious.

00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:05.340 align:middle line:84%
And the critical-- so just
think of it as a band.

00:22:05.340 --> 00:22:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:22:05.840 --> 00:22:08.048 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So the critical
faculty develops over time,

00:22:08.048 --> 00:22:10.530 align:middle line:90%
it's good that we have this.

00:22:10.530 --> 00:22:12.850 align:middle line:84%
I remember I grew up
here in Los Angeles,

00:22:12.850 --> 00:22:15.350 align:middle line:84%
and when I was four years old,
I jumped off the second story

00:22:15.350 --> 00:22:18.386 align:middle line:84%
building of my house because
I thought I could fly.

00:22:18.386 --> 00:22:19.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:22:19.180 --> 00:22:21.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And I
realized very quickly

00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:23.362 align:middle line:90%
that I couldn't fly, yet.

00:22:23.362 --> 00:22:23.862 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:22:23.862 --> 00:22:25.335 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:22:25.335 --> 00:22:26.600 align:middle line:90%
Where did you land?

00:22:26.600 --> 00:22:27.350 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Exactly.

00:22:27.350 --> 00:22:28.720 align:middle line:84%
So we develop this
critical faculty,

00:22:28.720 --> 00:22:29.860 align:middle line:90%
and it's a good thing to do--

00:22:29.860 --> 00:22:30.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:22:30.040 --> 00:22:30.880 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -that we have
this critical faculty.

00:22:30.880 --> 00:22:31.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:22:31.160 --> 00:22:31.300 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:22:31.300 --> 00:22:31.800 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:22:31.800 --> 00:22:32.325 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:22:32.325 --> 00:22:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: But when you're
a kid, everything's

00:22:34.200 --> 00:22:34.915 align:middle line:90%
imagine and pretend.

00:22:34.915 --> 00:22:35.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:22:35.190 --> 00:22:36.660 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And it's as
if-- like my niece,

00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:38.210 align:middle line:84%
Brittany, when
she was young, she

00:22:38.210 --> 00:22:41.050 align:middle line:84%
had these two imaginary
friends, LaLa and Cuckoo.

00:22:41.050 --> 00:22:41.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:22:41.550 --> 00:22:43.270 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And I remember having
Thanksgiving dinner with her

00:22:43.270 --> 00:22:45.010 align:middle line:84%
and I said, are LaLa
and Cuckoo here,

00:22:45.010 --> 00:22:46.852 align:middle line:84%
and she said, yes,
they're right there.

00:22:46.852 --> 00:22:48.060 align:middle line:90%
And it's as if she saw them--

00:22:48.060 --> 00:22:48.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:22:48.600 --> 00:22:49.810 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -like they
were really right there.

00:22:49.810 --> 00:22:51.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we have
that imagination.

00:22:51.180 --> 00:22:52.340 align:middle line:90%
We have a powerful imagination.

00:22:52.340 --> 00:22:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: We have a
powerful imagination.

00:22:53.250 --> 00:22:55.230 align:middle line:84%
And when you see a hypnotic
stage show and somebody says,

00:22:55.230 --> 00:22:56.690 align:middle line:90%
see the tennis ball in my hand.

00:22:56.690 --> 00:22:57.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:22:57.200 --> 00:22:58.540 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And they
go, what color is it

00:22:58.540 --> 00:22:59.831 align:middle line:90%
and the person says it's green.

00:22:59.831 --> 00:23:02.170 align:middle line:84%
And they throw it in the air
and the person watches it--

00:23:02.170 --> 00:23:02.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:23:02.670 --> 00:23:03.400 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Right.

00:23:03.400 --> 00:23:05.233 align:middle line:84%
Do they really see a
tennis ball or are they

00:23:05.233 --> 00:23:09.220 align:middle line:84%
imagining and pretending so much
so that it's as if they saw it?

00:23:09.220 --> 00:23:11.877 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if-- can you use
this type of imagination

00:23:11.877 --> 00:23:13.710 align:middle line:84%
and this technique that
you're talking about

00:23:13.710 --> 00:23:16.240 align:middle line:84%
to create more
wealth in your life?

00:23:16.240 --> 00:23:17.410 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Absolutely.

00:23:17.410 --> 00:23:20.360 align:middle line:84%
And here's the thing,
is because when

00:23:20.360 --> 00:23:22.990 align:middle line:84%
you take a technique
like affirmations.

00:23:22.990 --> 00:23:24.400 align:middle line:90%
People use affirmations.

00:23:24.400 --> 00:23:26.410 align:middle line:84%
But the purpose
of an affirmation

00:23:26.410 --> 00:23:30.471 align:middle line:84%
is to change a belief or a
value around a given subject.

00:23:30.471 --> 00:23:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you're
making affirmations

00:23:31.970 --> 00:23:32.840 align:middle line:84%
because you want
to make more money.

00:23:32.840 --> 00:23:34.700 align:middle line:84%
I bel-- and you're
saying-- basically,

00:23:34.700 --> 00:23:36.650 align:middle line:84%
what you're doing is you're
attempting to bludgeon your way

00:23:36.650 --> 00:23:39.110 align:middle line:84%
through the critical faculty
to the unconscious mind saying

00:23:39.110 --> 00:23:40.050 align:middle line:90%
believe this, believe this--

00:23:40.050 --> 00:23:40.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:23:40.460 --> 00:23:41.751 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: -believe this, right?

00:23:41.751 --> 00:23:43.560 align:middle line:84%
Now I remember running
on the beach when

00:23:43.560 --> 00:23:47.020 align:middle line:84%
I was living in El Porto,
California, broke, right?

00:23:47.020 --> 00:23:49.020 align:middle line:84%
Saying, you know, God's
wealth is flowing to me.

00:23:49.020 --> 00:23:50.560 align:middle line:84%
Money's coming to
me, I know it is.

00:23:50.560 --> 00:23:51.160 align:middle line:90%
I know it is.

00:23:51.160 --> 00:23:52.610 align:middle line:90%
It's going to come in.

00:23:52.610 --> 00:23:54.430 align:middle line:84%
And the problem with
that is that you've

00:23:54.430 --> 00:23:56.610 align:middle line:84%
got to chip your way through
this critical faculty

00:23:56.610 --> 00:23:58.060 align:middle line:90%
that you've developed over time.

00:23:58.060 --> 00:23:58.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:23:58.980 --> 00:24:01.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Now in
hypnosis, what we do

00:24:01.130 --> 00:24:02.587 align:middle line:84%
is we remove the
critical faculty

00:24:02.587 --> 00:24:04.920 align:middle line:84%
and we send you back to what
we call the imprint period.

00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:06.753 align:middle line:84%
The imprint period,
according to sociologist

00:24:06.753 --> 00:24:10.440 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Morris Massey
was age 0 to 7.

00:24:10.440 --> 00:24:12.716 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the neurology
in your body's firing

00:24:12.716 --> 00:24:13.340 align:middle line:90%
off like crazy.

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:17.510 align:middle line:84%
The average baby makes 20
billion synaptic connections

00:24:17.510 --> 00:24:18.610 align:middle line:90%
every single day.

00:24:18.610 --> 00:24:20.100 align:middle line:84%
That's about five
million a second.

00:24:20.100 --> 00:24:20.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:24:20.600 --> 00:24:22.355 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So the
neurology is firing off.

00:24:22.355 --> 00:24:23.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:24:23.100 --> 00:24:24.535 align:middle line:84%
And we think they're
just staring.

00:24:24.535 --> 00:24:25.160 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:24:25.160 --> 00:24:25.996 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, we think
they're just staring,

00:24:25.996 --> 00:24:27.780 align:middle line:84%
but they're like a little
sponge soaking things in.

00:24:27.780 --> 00:24:29.440 align:middle line:84%
That's my kids are such
exquisite learners.

00:24:29.440 --> 00:24:29.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:24:29.980 --> 00:24:30.410 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: They literally--

00:24:30.410 --> 00:24:31.104 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So fast.

00:24:31.104 --> 00:24:32.020 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: -soak it in.

00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:34.546 align:middle line:84%
They're programmed,
they're conditioned--

00:24:34.546 --> 00:24:38.150 align:middle line:84%
they become literally a replica
of their parents at that age.

00:24:38.150 --> 00:24:40.640 align:middle line:84%
Then they go out and they
find social models and stuff

00:24:40.640 --> 00:24:43.309 align:middle line:84%
like that, like you
did in modeling Oprah.

00:24:43.309 --> 00:24:43.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:24:43.850 --> 00:24:46.632 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So there is modeling
that happens beyond that,

00:24:46.632 --> 00:24:48.840 align:middle line:84%
but in the beginning, you're
like this little sponge.

00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:50.256 align:middle line:84%
Well, what we do
in hypnosis is we

00:24:50.256 --> 00:24:52.740 align:middle line:84%
get rid of the critical
faculty so that we can send you

00:24:52.740 --> 00:24:54.198 align:middle line:84%
back to that stage
where you become

00:24:54.198 --> 00:24:56.614 align:middle line:84%
like that little sponge
for selective suggestions.

00:24:56.614 --> 00:24:57.780 align:middle line:90%
And that's really important.

00:24:57.780 --> 00:24:59.815 align:middle line:84%
In a stage show, it has
to do with intentions,

00:24:59.815 --> 00:25:01.730 align:middle line:84%
to entertain or see how
far you can take it.

00:25:01.730 --> 00:25:02.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:25:02.050 --> 00:25:03.290 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: In
therapeutic hypnosis,

00:25:03.290 --> 00:25:04.765 align:middle line:84%
you're going to accept
suggestions that are

00:25:04.765 --> 00:25:06.800 align:middle line:84%
in alignment with-- if you're
coming to me to say you want

00:25:06.800 --> 00:25:07.330 align:middle line:90%
to make more money--

00:25:07.330 --> 00:25:08.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:25:08.090 --> 00:25:08.740 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -I'm
assuming you're going

00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:10.853 align:middle line:84%
to accept those
suggestions, once we get rid

00:25:10.853 --> 00:25:11.420 align:middle line:90%
of the critical faculty.

00:25:11.420 --> 00:25:12.860 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to stand
on your chair and bark

00:25:12.860 --> 00:25:14.120 align:middle line:84%
like a dog or
quack like a duck--

00:25:14.120 --> 00:25:14.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:25:14.500 --> 00:25:15.420 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: -or any of
those types of things,

00:25:15.420 --> 00:25:16.970 align:middle line:90%
because that's not why you came.

00:25:16.970 --> 00:25:18.771 align:middle line:84%
That's not what
the intention is.

00:25:18.771 --> 00:25:19.520 align:middle line:90%
So that's really--

00:25:19.520 --> 00:25:20.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK, so--

00:25:20.230 --> 00:25:20.640 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: -important, too.

00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:22.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I form my intention
before I get to you

00:25:22.790 --> 00:25:25.840 align:middle line:84%
and I say this is-- I don't
sit there and say, I am rich.

00:25:25.840 --> 00:25:28.830 align:middle line:84%
I sit there and
find out how I would

00:25:28.830 --> 00:25:31.095 align:middle line:84%
have various revenues
of income and what

00:25:31.095 --> 00:25:32.595 align:middle line:84%
I could change in
terms of my state.

00:25:32.595 --> 00:25:34.720 align:middle line:90%
Does that matter?

00:25:34.720 --> 00:25:36.650 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Both of those
things come into play

00:25:36.650 --> 00:25:41.110 align:middle line:84%
because your self-concept, I
am, your self-concept determines

00:25:41.110 --> 00:25:43.420 align:middle line:90%
everything in your life.

00:25:43.420 --> 00:25:46.340 align:middle line:84%
Whether you perceived yourself
to be a rich man, a beggar

00:25:46.340 --> 00:25:49.620 align:middle line:84%
man, a poor man or a thief,
that determines everything.

00:25:49.620 --> 00:25:51.480 align:middle line:84%
So it all starts
with self-concept.

00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:55.840 align:middle line:84%
But saying it is a far
cry from owning it.

00:25:55.840 --> 00:25:56.455 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:25:56.455 --> 00:25:58.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: It's like Morpheus
said to Neo in "The Matrix."

00:25:58.830 --> 00:26:00.050 align:middle line:84%
There's a difference
between knowing the path

00:26:00.050 --> 00:26:01.230 align:middle line:90%
and walking the path.

00:26:01.230 --> 00:26:01.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:26:01.730 --> 00:26:04.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And so that-- and
therein lies the challenge.

00:26:04.250 --> 00:26:06.000 align:middle line:84%
With traditional
affirmations, we

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:08.040 align:middle line:84%
would be saying it,
attempting to make it

00:26:08.040 --> 00:26:09.550 align:middle line:90%
through the critical faculty.

00:26:09.550 --> 00:26:11.636 align:middle line:90%
Owning it is a different thing.

00:26:11.636 --> 00:26:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And we get rid of
the critical faculty,

00:26:13.260 --> 00:26:15.343 align:middle line:84%
just like when my niece
Brittany saw a LaLa-- yes,

00:26:15.343 --> 00:26:17.630 align:middle line:84%
they're right there,
LaLa and Cuckoo, that's

00:26:17.630 --> 00:26:19.380 align:middle line:90%
when we can own it.

00:26:19.380 --> 00:26:23.140 align:middle line:84%
And so Dr. Erickson said
my best hypnotic subject

00:26:23.140 --> 00:26:27.340 align:middle line:84%
became my best hypnotic subject
after 300 repeated inductions.

00:26:27.340 --> 00:26:27.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:30.400 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: What that means
is not that they weren't

00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:32.386 align:middle line:84%
