00:34:02.430 --> 00:34:04.550 align:middle line:90%
empowering states for you?

00:34:04.550 --> 00:34:06.990 align:middle line:84%
What's a state that you want
to be in in relationship

00:34:06.990 --> 00:34:08.170 align:middle line:90%
to this family member?

00:34:08.170 --> 00:34:09.929 align:middle line:90%
Is it a state of compassion?

00:34:09.929 --> 00:34:10.551 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps.

00:34:10.551 --> 00:34:13.050 align:middle line:84%
Is it a state of understanding,
and I don't know what it is.

00:34:13.050 --> 00:34:15.360 align:middle line:84%
It's like it's going
to be different

00:34:15.360 --> 00:34:18.326 align:middle line:84%
depending upon the
situation, the individual,

00:34:18.326 --> 00:34:20.409 align:middle line:84%
so you're the one that has
to decide these things.

00:34:20.409 --> 00:34:22.360 align:middle line:84%
But what are the
states that you really

00:34:22.360 --> 00:34:23.940 align:middle line:84%
want to bring into
that situation?

00:34:23.940 --> 00:34:27.150 align:middle line:84%
I think that most people go
through life getting whatever

00:34:27.150 --> 00:34:30.239 align:middle line:84%
they get emotionally,
and they're

00:34:30.239 --> 00:34:32.500 align:middle line:84%
at the whim of everything
else that happens to them.

00:34:32.500 --> 00:34:33.000 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:35.560 align:middle line:84%
Now what I'm suggesting
is rather than

00:34:35.560 --> 00:34:38.964 align:middle line:84%
do that, you go into
situations by design.

00:34:38.964 --> 00:34:41.130 align:middle line:84%
That you go into these
situations and you think, OK,

00:34:41.130 --> 00:34:42.770 align:middle line:84%
what are the emotional
states that I'm

00:34:42.770 --> 00:34:44.500 align:middle line:84%
going to bring into
this situation?

00:34:44.500 --> 00:34:47.820 align:middle line:84%
Now one thing to remember is
that when you are in any given

00:34:47.820 --> 00:34:50.750 align:middle line:84%
situation, in interpersonal
communication the person

00:34:50.750 --> 00:34:53.159 align:middle line:84%
who's most committed
to their state

00:34:53.159 --> 00:34:56.449 align:middle line:84%
will end up drawing the
other person into that state.

00:34:56.449 --> 00:34:59.110 align:middle line:84%
So if this family
member is more committed

00:34:59.110 --> 00:35:02.606 align:middle line:84%
to whatever emotional state
they're in, whether it be--

00:35:02.606 --> 00:35:04.980 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know what they're
doing to push your buttons,

00:35:04.980 --> 00:35:08.850 align:middle line:84%
so you say, but maybe
they're irritated

00:35:08.850 --> 00:35:10.560 align:middle line:90%
or they're agitated in some way.

00:35:10.560 --> 00:35:12.250 align:middle line:84%
Well, if they're more
committed to that

00:35:12.250 --> 00:35:15.030 align:middle line:84%
than you are to the states that
you're going to go in with,

00:35:15.030 --> 00:35:18.772 align:middle line:84%
like a state of compassion
or a state of love.

00:35:18.772 --> 00:35:20.480 align:middle line:84%
If they're more
committed to their state,

00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:21.980 align:middle line:84%
they're going to
pull you in, right?

00:35:21.980 --> 00:35:24.490 align:middle line:84%
If you're committed more to
your state, on the other hand,

00:35:24.490 --> 00:35:25.990 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
pull them in, right?

00:35:25.990 --> 00:35:28.890 align:middle line:84%
So that's the key
is first deciding

00:35:28.890 --> 00:35:30.550 align:middle line:84%
what emotional
states do you want

00:35:30.550 --> 00:35:32.390 align:middle line:84%
to be in when you go
into that situation?

00:35:32.390 --> 00:35:35.280 align:middle line:84%
Write down three or four
different empowering states.

00:35:35.280 --> 00:35:37.550 align:middle line:84%
And then when I say come
up with some triggers that

00:35:37.550 --> 00:35:40.110 align:middle line:84%
can trigger those states off,
maybe what you want to do

00:35:40.110 --> 00:35:42.100 align:middle line:84%
is just reconditioning
the old triggers.

00:35:42.100 --> 00:35:43.340 align:middle line:90%
That's a good way to go.

00:35:43.340 --> 00:35:47.010 align:middle line:84%
So you can do this through
visual guided imagery, right?

00:35:47.010 --> 00:35:49.430 align:middle line:90%
Now it's a complex process.

00:35:49.430 --> 00:35:51.430 align:middle line:84%
We teach all sorts of
different ways to do this.

00:35:51.430 --> 00:35:55.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to give you the
down and dirty quick way

00:35:55.310 --> 00:35:59.320 align:middle line:84%
to reprogram or recondition
those anchors that you

00:35:59.320 --> 00:36:00.520 align:middle line:90%
have that fire off.

00:36:00.520 --> 00:36:03.120 align:middle line:84%
So one way would
be, first of all, we

00:36:03.120 --> 00:36:05.620 align:middle line:84%
need to collect those
emotional states.

00:36:05.620 --> 00:36:07.880 align:middle line:84%
So whatever emotional
states you write down,

00:36:07.880 --> 00:36:11.180 align:middle line:84%
let's say it's compassion, it's
love, and it's understanding.

00:36:11.180 --> 00:36:13.900 align:middle line:84%
Then I want you to write
down three or four events

00:36:13.900 --> 00:36:15.820 align:middle line:84%
in your past for
each one of those

00:36:15.820 --> 00:36:18.250 align:middle line:84%
where you felt those
emotional states.

00:36:18.250 --> 00:36:20.860 align:middle line:84%
So write down three or
four events from your past

00:36:20.860 --> 00:36:23.360 align:middle line:84%
for each one of those where you
felt those emotional states.

00:36:23.360 --> 00:36:25.190 align:middle line:90%
Step one, identify the states.

00:36:25.190 --> 00:36:28.260 align:middle line:84%
Step two, write down three
or four events from your past

00:36:28.260 --> 00:36:29.770 align:middle line:90%
where you felt those states.

00:36:29.770 --> 00:36:34.050 align:middle line:84%
Step three, go back into those
incidents, like in your mind,

00:36:34.050 --> 00:36:36.250 align:middle line:90%
it's a journey of consciousness.

00:36:36.250 --> 00:36:38.990 align:middle line:84%
But all of your problems
are problems of imagination,

00:36:38.990 --> 00:36:41.730 align:middle line:84%
and all of your solutions
are solutions of imagination.

00:36:41.730 --> 00:36:42.600 align:middle line:84%
So you're going to
go back and you're

00:36:42.600 --> 00:36:44.270 align:middle line:84%
going to step into your
body so you're right

00:36:44.270 --> 00:36:46.880 align:middle line:84%
inside those events, so you're
looking through your own eyes,

00:36:46.880 --> 00:36:48.296 align:middle line:84%
hearing what you
heard at the time

00:36:48.296 --> 00:36:49.710 align:middle line:90%
and feeling those feelings.

00:36:49.710 --> 00:36:51.400 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to
collect those states

00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:54.996 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to begin to
practice feeling those states.

00:36:54.996 --> 00:36:56.370 align:middle line:84%
We have a technique
that's called

00:36:56.370 --> 00:36:58.592 align:middle line:84%
stacking that we teach also
in some of our trainings,

00:36:58.592 --> 00:37:01.050 align:middle line:84%
where you can go back and you
can stack one of those states

00:37:01.050 --> 00:37:02.460 align:middle line:84%
on top of another
on top of another

00:37:02.460 --> 00:37:04.584 align:middle line:84%
so you could be feeling
three or four those states.

00:37:04.584 --> 00:37:06.280 align:middle line:84%
So you could be
feeling compassionate

00:37:06.280 --> 00:37:08.020 align:middle line:90%
and loving at the same time.

00:37:08.020 --> 00:37:13.560 align:middle line:84%
And you're feeling
healthily detached,

00:37:13.560 --> 00:37:16.060 align:middle line:84%
might be a good state to
bring in there, too, right?

00:37:16.060 --> 00:37:18.510 align:middle line:84%
So where you're feeling
all of those things, right?

00:37:18.510 --> 00:37:21.160 align:middle line:90%
So you can stack those.

00:37:21.160 --> 00:37:23.080 align:middle line:84%
The way that you do it
is you feel one state,

00:37:23.080 --> 00:37:25.310 align:middle line:84%
you go into another
event with another state

00:37:25.310 --> 00:37:27.440 align:middle line:84%
and then you just imagine
stacking that state

00:37:27.440 --> 00:37:28.440 align:middle line:90%
on top of the first one.

00:37:28.440 --> 00:37:30.690 align:middle line:84%
And then you can do the same
thing with the third one.

00:37:30.690 --> 00:37:33.030 align:middle line:84%
And you'll get better
at layering these states

00:37:33.030 --> 00:37:33.790 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:37:33.790 --> 00:37:35.975 align:middle line:84%
Once you've done all
of that, then you

00:37:35.975 --> 00:37:37.350 align:middle line:84%
can come back to
the here and now

00:37:37.350 --> 00:37:40.640 align:middle line:84%
and then just do guided imagery
and do visual rehearsal.

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:43.770 align:middle line:84%
Imagine yourself going into
situations with this person

00:37:43.770 --> 00:37:46.350 align:middle line:84%
where they do whatever they
did that fired off those-- that

00:37:46.350 --> 00:37:49.330 align:middle line:84%
