00:41:42.110 --> 00:41:44.193 align:middle line:84%
nothing that could happen
to me in business that's

00:41:44.193 --> 00:41:46.330 align:middle line:84%
worth worrying about,
which tells you something

00:41:46.330 --> 00:41:47.920 align:middle line:84%
about his values,
tells you something

00:41:47.920 --> 00:41:49.870 align:middle line:90%
about what's really important.

00:41:49.870 --> 00:41:51.610 align:middle line:84%
He said, if there
was something that

00:41:51.610 --> 00:41:54.295 align:middle line:84%
was to happen to either
my health or the health

00:41:54.295 --> 00:41:56.540 align:middle line:84%
of somebody in my family,
that would be a problem.

00:41:56.540 --> 00:41:58.270 align:middle line:84%
But there's nothing that could
happen to me in business.

00:41:58.270 --> 00:41:59.360 align:middle line:84%
And I know you had
direct experiences

00:41:59.360 --> 00:41:59.780 align:middle line:90%
with things like that.

00:41:59.780 --> 00:42:00.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:42:00.570 --> 00:42:01.070 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:42:01.070 --> 00:42:01.450 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: He said,
there's nothing

00:42:01.450 --> 00:42:02.400 align:middle line:84%
that could happen
to me in business

00:42:02.400 --> 00:42:03.150 align:middle line:90%
that's worth worrying about.

00:42:03.150 --> 00:42:04.295 align:middle line:84%
He said, if the
Virgin companies were

00:42:04.295 --> 00:42:06.150 align:middle line:84%
to fall out from
underneath me today,

00:42:06.150 --> 00:42:08.100 align:middle line:90%
I go move to Bali or something.

00:42:08.100 --> 00:42:09.267 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So you went to Bali.

00:42:09.267 --> 00:42:09.891 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:42:09.891 --> 00:42:11.860 align:middle line:84%
The funny thing is, I
had been seeing pictures

00:42:11.860 --> 00:42:14.780 align:middle line:84%
from Bali, because I used to
work in Club Med in the hotel

00:42:14.780 --> 00:42:17.120 align:middle line:84%
resort industry and I saw
pictures of this paradise.

00:42:17.120 --> 00:42:18.160 align:middle line:90%
You know, like--

00:42:18.160 --> 00:42:19.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Of course, the
huts and everything.

00:42:19.040 --> 00:42:19.310 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:42:19.310 --> 00:42:21.184 align:middle line:84%
They have a resort out
there and I had always

00:42:21.184 --> 00:42:23.440 align:middle line:84%
wanted to go anyway and
I heard him say that.

00:42:23.440 --> 00:42:26.910 align:middle line:84%
And then I got to this point
where I just desperately needed

00:42:26.910 --> 00:42:28.769 align:middle line:84%
a break, and I had
a hostile takeover

00:42:28.769 --> 00:42:29.810 align:middle line:90%
with my business partner.

00:42:29.810 --> 00:42:31.935 align:middle line:84%
All sorts of weird stuff
happened with the company.

00:42:31.935 --> 00:42:35.120 align:middle line:84%
It was like, OK, I'm stepping
out and I packed my bags

00:42:35.120 --> 00:42:36.170 align:middle line:90%
and I went to Bali.

00:42:36.170 --> 00:42:37.836 align:middle line:90%
And I grew my hair long.

00:42:37.836 --> 00:42:39.210 align:middle line:84%
You know, all my
shots everywhere

00:42:39.210 --> 00:42:41.180 align:middle line:84%
you see short hair on
the book, and it's like,

00:42:41.180 --> 00:42:44.010 align:middle line:84%
I grew my hair long-- the
jury's still out on it,

00:42:44.010 --> 00:42:46.820 align:middle line:84%
but I grew it long and
I'm riding my motorcycle

00:42:46.820 --> 00:42:50.490 align:middle line:84%
through the rainforests and
just connecting, just being.

00:42:50.490 --> 00:42:51.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Letting go.

00:42:51.350 --> 00:42:52.100 align:middle line:90%
Not caring.

00:42:52.100 --> 00:42:52.410 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Letting go.

00:42:52.410 --> 00:42:52.910 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:42:52.910 --> 00:42:56.380 align:middle line:84%
And you really do realize
what's really important.

00:42:56.380 --> 00:42:58.082 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's like
Walt Disney said,

00:42:58.082 --> 00:42:59.540 align:middle line:84%
we don't make movies
to make money,

00:42:59.540 --> 00:43:00.770 align:middle line:90%
we make money to make movies.

00:43:00.770 --> 00:43:02.228 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what's
really important?

00:43:02.228 --> 00:43:06.160 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Well, for me, like--
and, you ask me tomorrow,

00:43:06.160 --> 00:43:07.910 align:middle line:90%
ask me in another 100 years.

00:43:07.910 --> 00:43:09.190 align:middle line:90%
It changes from time to time.

00:43:09.190 --> 00:43:09.731 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:09.731 --> 00:43:12.430 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: But I think
for each of us--

00:43:12.430 --> 00:43:15.100 align:middle line:84%
Viktor Frankl wrote his book
"Man's Search For Meaning"

00:43:15.100 --> 00:43:17.904 align:middle line:84%
and he said we're all looking
to have meaning in our life,

00:43:17.904 --> 00:43:20.320 align:middle line:84%
and we need to have-- you know,
people that live in states

00:43:20.320 --> 00:43:22.600 align:middle line:84%
of chronic depression and
things like that is oftentimes

00:43:22.600 --> 00:43:23.390 align:middle line:84%
because they don't
have a greater

00:43:23.390 --> 00:43:24.870 align:middle line:84%
meaning to their
experience of life.

00:43:24.870 --> 00:43:25.411 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right

00:43:25.411 --> 00:43:27.980 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And for me,
up until that time,

00:43:27.980 --> 00:43:29.520 align:middle line:90%
my meaning was the mission.

00:43:29.520 --> 00:43:31.980 align:middle line:84%
Pursuing the mission and
making a global difference,

00:43:31.980 --> 00:43:34.630 align:middle line:84%
and then eradicating
poverty on a larger level.

00:43:34.630 --> 00:43:36.910 align:middle line:84%
So I felt like I was
on this big mission.

00:43:36.910 --> 00:43:39.517 align:middle line:84%
But I poured so much of
myself into that mission

00:43:39.517 --> 00:43:40.850 align:middle line:90%
that I was like a shooting star.

00:43:40.850 --> 00:43:43.050 align:middle line:84%
So it was like when I
got back out to Bali,

00:43:43.050 --> 00:43:45.700 align:middle line:84%
I got to discover myself and
my relationship with myself.

00:43:45.700 --> 00:43:47.670 align:middle line:84%
And then it was like-- OK,
so I went through this phase

00:43:47.670 --> 00:43:49.420 align:middle line:84%
where I was like, OK, I'm
what's really important.

00:43:49.420 --> 00:43:50.295 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's like--

00:43:50.295 --> 00:43:51.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very good, yes.

00:43:51.460 --> 00:43:53.251 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Yeah, it's
like-- because nothing

00:43:53.251 --> 00:43:57.530 align:middle line:84%
exists without me because who
knows what happens when we go.

00:43:57.530 --> 00:44:00.570 align:middle line:84%
So all I wanted to do was
enjoy myself and just have fun.

00:44:00.570 --> 00:44:03.010 align:middle line:84%
But then there was this
burning inside of me

00:44:03.010 --> 00:44:05.950 align:middle line:84%
again to get back out and it's
like, OK, I'm going to do this

00:44:05.950 --> 00:44:07.740 align:middle line:84%
but I'm going to do
it in a different way.

00:44:07.740 --> 00:44:11.970 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to do it in
respecting myself and taking

00:44:11.970 --> 00:44:13.800 align:middle line:84%
care of myself along
the way, not being

00:44:13.800 --> 00:44:17.610 align:middle line:84%
a martyr for the cause,
but building in a way.

00:44:17.610 --> 00:44:19.069 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's--
it's maturing.

00:44:19.069 --> 00:44:19.568 align:middle line:90%
It's--

00:44:19.568 --> 00:44:21.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're a personal
development story

00:44:21.360 --> 00:44:22.860 align:middle line:84%
within a personal
development story.

00:44:22.860 --> 00:44:23.693 align:middle line:90%
That's what you are.

00:44:23.693 --> 00:44:24.610 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:24.610 --> 00:44:25.860 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Thank God, you know.

00:44:25.860 --> 00:44:26.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's great.

00:44:26.930 --> 00:44:27.640 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Yeah.

00:44:27.640 --> 00:44:28.840 align:middle line:84%
And people have been
telling me that lately.

00:44:28.840 --> 00:44:31.575 align:middle line:84%
They're coming up to me like,
oh my God, to watch the grace

00:44:31.575 --> 00:44:33.450 align:middle line:84%
and elegance that you
came through this with.

00:44:33.450 --> 00:44:35.780 align:middle line:84%
If only they knew behind
closed doors, right?

00:44:35.780 --> 00:44:38.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you were just
recently doing another class

00:44:38.530 --> 00:44:42.030 align:middle line:84%
here in Los Angeles and we
have another video clip.

00:44:42.030 --> 00:44:44.050 align:middle line:84%
And tell us a little
bit about what this is?

00:44:44.050 --> 00:44:47.450 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: So this is actually
a pain control demonstration

00:44:47.450 --> 00:44:50.300 align:middle line:84%
that I did just
this past weekend.

00:44:50.300 --> 00:44:53.560 align:middle line:84%
And in this, I use
a rapid induction,

00:44:53.560 --> 00:44:55.300 align:middle line:90%
which looks actually very harsh.

00:44:55.300 --> 00:44:57.430 align:middle line:84%
It looks like I'm karate
chopping her on the neck.

00:44:57.430 --> 00:44:59.638 align:middle line:84%
But it actually goes-- so
it's a rapid induction that

00:44:59.638 --> 00:45:01.730 align:middle line:84%
takes her very, very
deep very quick.

00:45:01.730 --> 00:45:04.900 align:middle line:84%
But she will rate her pain
on a scale from zero to 100.

00:45:04.900 --> 00:45:06.400 align:middle line:84%
She'll have a certain
amount of pain

00:45:06.400 --> 00:45:07.890 align:middle line:84%
and then that pain
will dissipate

00:45:07.890 --> 00:45:10.120 align:middle line:84%
after we do the
induction in the process.

00:45:10.120 --> 00:45:12.320 align:middle line:84%
Now the thing is is
that with pain control,

00:45:12.320 --> 00:45:14.090 align:middle line:84%
I did that all
across North America,

00:45:14.090 --> 00:45:15.790 align:middle line:84%
taught it for years
and years and years,

00:45:15.790 --> 00:45:19.390 align:middle line:84%
and hypnosis is one
most phenomenal methods

00:45:19.390 --> 00:45:21.030 align:middle line:84%
that I've ever seen
for pain control.

00:45:21.030 --> 00:45:22.905 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's beautiful
because there are so

00:45:22.905 --> 00:45:25.324 align:middle line:84%
many people in pain,
especially back pain.

00:45:25.324 --> 00:45:26.740 align:middle line:84%
So let's take a
look at this clip.

00:45:26.740 --> 00:45:27.684 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:45:27.684 --> 00:45:28.350 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:45:28.350 --> 00:45:31.900 align:middle line:84%
-And you're going to
push down on my hand.

00:45:31.900 --> 00:45:35.089 align:middle line:84%
And as you push down
on my hand, you're

00:45:35.089 --> 00:45:36.755 align:middle line:84%
going to push as hard
as you can and I'm

00:45:36.755 --> 00:45:39.050 align:middle line:84%
going to count from
one to whatever.

00:45:39.050 --> 00:45:43.766 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to double the
pressure with every count.

00:45:43.766 --> 00:45:44.704 align:middle line:90%
Are you ready?

00:45:44.704 --> 00:45:46.370 align:middle line:84%
Now while you're
pushing with your hand,

00:45:46.370 --> 00:45:48.004 align:middle line:84%
I want your eyes
to look up here.

00:45:48.004 --> 00:45:49.891 align:middle line:90%
Bring your eyes up here, OK?

00:45:49.891 --> 00:45:52.140 align:middle line:84%
So go ahead and begin to
push down as hard as you can.

00:45:52.140 --> 00:45:53.690 align:middle line:90%
Hard, hard, one.

00:45:53.690 --> 00:45:54.960 align:middle line:90%
Double, two.

00:45:54.960 --> 00:45:56.190 align:middle line:90%
Double, three.

00:45:56.190 --> 00:45:57.651 align:middle line:90%
Double, good, four.

00:45:57.651 --> 00:45:58.446 align:middle line:90%
Double it.

00:45:58.446 --> 00:45:59.112 align:middle line:90%
Close your eyes.

00:45:59.112 --> 00:46:00.573 align:middle line:90%
Four, double it.

00:46:00.573 --> 00:46:01.400 align:middle line:90%
Five, double it.

00:46:01.400 --> 00:46:03.620 align:middle line:84%
And sleep, sleep, sleep,
sleep, sleep, sleep, sleep.

00:46:03.620 --> 00:46:04.390 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:06.008 align:middle line:90%
All the way down.

00:46:06.008 --> 00:46:07.960 align:middle line:90%
All the way down.

00:46:07.960 --> 00:46:11.160 align:middle line:84%
I want you to find
yourself right now

00:46:11.160 --> 00:46:17.070 align:middle line:84%
walking in a wondrous
winter wonderland.

00:46:17.070 --> 00:46:20.605 align:middle line:84%
It's cold outside, so you can
see your breath in the air.

00:46:20.605 --> 00:46:22.382 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:46:22.382 --> 00:46:24.590 align:middle line:84%
As you're walking in this
wondrous winter wonderland,

00:46:24.590 --> 00:46:29.070 align:middle line:84%
you can feel the snow
collapse beneath your feet.

00:46:29.070 --> 00:46:33.250 align:middle line:84%
You're walking through this
wondrous winter wonderland.

00:46:33.250 --> 00:46:35.198 align:middle line:90%
Your breath is there.

00:46:35.198 --> 00:46:38.607 align:middle line:84%
You're bundled up nice
and warm so it feels good.

00:46:38.607 --> 00:46:42.990 align:middle line:84%
If that right hand was
completely anesthetized now,

00:46:42.990 --> 00:46:47.164 align:middle line:84%
what's the color of that
anesthesia in that right hand?

00:46:47.164 --> 00:46:48.601 align:middle line:90%
Imagine if it had a color.

00:46:48.601 --> 00:46:51.516 align:middle line:90%
Imagine if it made a sound.

00:46:51.516 --> 00:46:54.580 align:middle line:84%
And imagine a feeling
of anesthesia.

00:46:54.580 --> 00:46:59.060 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to begin to
flow a river of anesthesia

00:46:59.060 --> 00:47:02.730 align:middle line:84%
from your right hand all the way
up your right arm, all the way

00:47:02.730 --> 00:47:06.220 align:middle line:84%
over to your back to that area
where you require healing.

00:47:06.220 --> 00:47:08.620 align:middle line:84%
Allowing the river of
anesthesia to continue

00:47:08.620 --> 00:47:13.095 align:middle line:84%
to flow to your back to that
area where you require healing.

00:47:13.095 --> 00:47:15.820 align:middle line:84%
Your lower back, all the
way down through the leg,

00:47:15.820 --> 00:47:17.860 align:middle line:84%
wherever it is that
you require healing.

00:47:17.860 --> 00:47:20.380 align:middle line:84%
Imagine the color and
the sound and the feeling

00:47:20.380 --> 00:47:25.710 align:middle line:84%
of anesthesia flowing down
to that area, saturating it.

00:47:25.710 --> 00:47:28.440 align:middle line:84%
You'll find it easy to
respond while remaining deeply

00:47:28.440 --> 00:47:31.640 align:middle line:84%
in trance, on a scale
from zero to 100

00:47:31.640 --> 00:47:34.400 align:middle line:90%
right now, where are you now?

00:47:34.400 --> 00:47:37.170 align:middle line:90%


00:47:37.170 --> 00:47:37.700 align:middle line:90%
-40.

00:47:37.700 --> 00:47:38.585 align:middle line:90%
-40.

00:47:38.585 --> 00:47:39.084 align:middle line:90%
Perfect.

00:47:39.084 --> 00:47:41.740 align:middle line:90%
That's the perfect number.

00:47:41.740 --> 00:47:44.320 align:middle line:84%
I want you to continue to
flow that river of anesthesia.

00:47:44.320 --> 00:47:46.680 align:middle line:90%
It's faster than a Tylenol.

00:47:46.680 --> 00:47:48.820 align:middle line:84%
Continue to flow that
river of anesthesia

00:47:48.820 --> 00:47:51.440 align:middle line:84%
from the right hand
down to that area,

00:47:51.440 --> 00:47:53.237 align:middle line:84%
completely
anesthetizing that area.

00:47:53.237 --> 00:47:55.195 align:middle line:84%
Imagining the color, the
sound, and the feeling

00:47:55.195 --> 00:47:57.470 align:middle line:84%
of that anesthesia
down there in those--

00:47:57.470 --> 00:47:59.283 align:middle line:84%
wherever it is that
you require healing.

00:47:59.283 --> 00:48:00.270 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK ENDS]

00:48:00.270 --> 00:48:02.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That was
absolutely magnificent.

00:48:02.460 --> 00:48:04.380 align:middle line:84%
People were talking
about that all weekend,

00:48:04.380 --> 00:48:06.200 align:middle line:90%
so it's very powerful process.

00:48:06.200 --> 00:48:08.200 align:middle line:84%
And did you check back
in with her the next day?

00:48:08.200 --> 00:48:08.908 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: We did.

00:48:08.908 --> 00:48:11.959 align:middle line:84%
So the pain had
gone down even more.

00:48:11.959 --> 00:48:13.750 align:middle line:84%
Like I think she was
at a two the next day,

00:48:13.750 --> 00:48:15.660 align:middle line:84%
and she had been
at an 80 before.

00:48:15.660 --> 00:48:16.584 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:48:16.584 --> 00:48:18.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: Yeah, but
that's not uncommon.

00:48:18.250 --> 00:48:20.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I would get that all the
time where people I would work

00:48:20.890 --> 00:48:23.176 align:middle line:84%
pain control with them and
years later they'd come up to me

00:48:23.176 --> 00:48:25.050 align:middle line:84%
and say, you know, I never
had pain again in my body.

00:48:25.050 --> 00:48:26.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It carries
over that long?

00:48:26.690 --> 00:48:27.460 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Not every time.

00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:29.793 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it becomes more of
a thing of pain management.

00:48:29.793 --> 00:48:30.540 align:middle line:90%
It just depends.

00:48:30.540 --> 00:48:34.180 align:middle line:84%
But it's just one example
of what we're capable of.

00:48:34.180 --> 00:48:34.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:48:34.680 --> 00:48:37.221 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And I think that's
the real important message here,

00:48:37.221 --> 00:48:40.464 align:middle line:84%
is not that we can put
somebody in a rapid trance

00:48:40.464 --> 00:48:41.880 align:middle line:84%
so they can get
rid of their pain.

00:48:41.880 --> 00:48:43.730 align:middle line:84%
But if they can do that,
what else can they do?

00:48:43.730 --> 00:48:44.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:48:44.140 --> 00:48:44.530 align:middle line:90%
What else?

00:48:44.530 --> 00:48:45.610 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: What else
are we capable of?

00:48:45.610 --> 00:48:46.820 align:middle line:90%
People play small in life.

00:48:46.820 --> 00:48:48.660 align:middle line:84%
We're capable of so much
more than we give ourselves

00:48:48.660 --> 00:48:49.160 align:middle line:90%
credit for.

00:48:49.160 --> 00:48:49.659 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:48:49.659 --> 00:48:51.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HOWARD: And when
we learn how to tap

00:48:51.250 --> 00:48:55.170 align:middle line:84%
into the power of
100% of who we are,

00:48:55.170 --> 00:48:57.660 align:middle line:84%
we can live the lives that
we're really meant to live.

00:48:57.660 --> 00:48:59.830 align:middle line:84%
We can live the highest
expression of a life

00:48:59.830 --> 00:49:01.627 align:middle line:84%
that we possibly
could live, and that's

00:49:01.627 --> 00:49:02.960 align:middle line:90%
why this stuff has been so cool.

00:49:02.960 --> 00:49:05.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Shows the beautiful
power of our minds.

00:49:05.080 --> 00:49:07.100 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much, Chris
Howard, for joining me.

00:49:07.100 --> 00:49:07.840 align:middle line:90%
>>HOWARD: Thank you.

